== Aircraft Flight Instruments

Modern aircraft rely on a standardized suite of flight instruments that allow
pilots to safely control and navigate the aircraft, especially under Instrument
Flight Rules (IFR). When outside visual references are limited or unavailable,
these instruments provide the information needed to maintain situational
awareness by indicating the aircraft's position, motion, and orientation.
Refined over decades, they form the foundation of safe and effective instrument
flying @transport_canada_tp9939e_2021.

== The Six Primary Flight Instruments
Rather than attempting to replicate all six instruments in full detail, this
project focuses on four core flight parameters: yaw, roll, pitch, and heading @mech4182_aerospace_structures @mech3520_aerodynamics.
These variables capture the essential aspects of aircraft orientation and
directional control while keeping the project scope manageable. A digital
display is also included to show the corresponding numerical values, providing
clearer feedback and improving usability. This approach balances realism with
practical design constraints while still demonstrating the key principles of
flight instrumentation. 

